# PropertyFlow Environment Configuration
# 
# SECURITY WARNING: Never commit actual secrets to version control.
# Use a .env file (local, git-ignored) for sensitive values.
#
# SERVER-SIDE ONLY (Node.js scripts):
# These values are used by local Node scripts only and are NEVER exposed to the browser.
#
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
# Optional for future server-side admin automation only. Never send this to the browser.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
SUPABASE_TEST_EMAIL=your-email@example.com
SUPABASE_TEST_PASSWORD=your-password
#
# BROWSER-SIDE:
# Browser credentials and mode are centralized in config.js.
# The browser must only ever use the anon/public key.
#
# APP MODE:
# Set appMode in config.js to one of:
# - 'supabase' for production/live mode
# - 'demo' for explicit local/offline mode
